subject: p16553329
History: With tremors consistent with past infections. On HD. No new electrolyte imbalance, eval for infectious etiology.
Findings: There has been interval placement of a right central dialysis catheter. Bilateral hilar vascular prominence is re-demonstrated with subtle nodularity in the left upper lung likely representing confluence of vasculature though a true nodule difficult to exclude. There is no convincing sign of pneumonia or overt edema. Small left effusion is present with basilar atelectasis. The cardiomediastinal silhouette is unchanged.
Impression: New HD catheter in place. Prominent perihilar vascular markings with subtle nodularity in the left upper lobe requiring CT on a nonemergent basis to further assess. Small left pleural effusion with basal atelectasis.
